post_text: The GM Student Council will be hosting a Mental Illness Awareness Breakfast along with a modified Warrior Dash (for those who want to participate)in honor of Treyton Ottman on Saturday, March 30th. The breakfast will be from 9-11 in the GM cafeteria & the Warrior Dash will start at 8:30 in Legacy Gym & then outside for the course. We are looking for people to perform for entertainment during the breakfast. Please contact Lisa Glynn if you are willing. (Singing, playing an instrument, showing a talent, etc).

Grand Meadow Student Council
text:
The GM Student Council will be hosting a Mental Illness Awareness Breakfast along with a modified Warrior Dash (for those who want to participate)in honor of Treyton Ottman on Saturday, March 30th. The breakfast will be from 9-11 in the GM cafeteria & the Warrior Dash will start at 8:30 in Legacy Gym & then outside for the course. We are looking for people to perform for entertainment during the breakfast. Please contact Lisa Glynn if you are willing. (Singing, playing an instrument, showing a talent, etc).

Grand Meadow Student Council

post_text: GM Student Council President Greta Warmka and Treasurer Kaitlyn Hilton present a check for $5,000 to the Milagros Vigo family. Milagros was diagnosed in late October with stage 4 uterine cancer which has spread to her lung, spine, two tumors in her brain along with one behind her eye. Her daughter Camil is a senior at Grand Meadow High School.

post_text: Valleyfair trip tomorrow (Monday)! Bus leaves at 8:30 am from in front of High School doors. Bring sunscreen, food or money if needed!
text: Valleyfair trip tomorrow (Monday)! Bus leaves at 8:30 am from in front of High School doors. Bring sunscreen, food or money if needed!

post_text:
We are excited for our trip to Valleyfair on Monday, June 8th. The bus will leave at 8:30 am from in front of the High School doors. Admission costs are covered but students will either need to bring their own lunch & snacks or bring money to buy food (things are pretty expensive there). Also dress appropriately for the weather - not sure what the forecast will be but remember sunscreen, sweatshirt if it's cold, umbrella & good walking shoes. We will be taking a school bus and a school van because some kids need to be home early. Our approximate arrival back in GM will be around 8:00 pm. If you are on the list and do not show up on Monday, you will be responsible for reimbursing the Student Council for the price of admission.

See you Monday!
Mrs. Glynn & Ms. Collins

Thank you for liking the Grand Meadow Student Council Facebook page. You will find all the information you need here.
We will be having our first official meeting next Thursday: August 7th at 6:30pm in Ms. Collins room. All of your parents have been emailed and added to an email list where they will always be notified about upcoming meetings. If you are unable to make it to one of the meetings you must contact one of the executive officers AT LEAST 24 hours prior to the meeting with a reasonable excuse. August 7th is an important meeting so please try your best to be there. Executive officers are Rachel Oehlke, Haley Krumm, Blake Olson and Allison Gehling.
See you all next Thursday! Thanks!
